  "texts": [
    "When colored by Plate IDs, the data points are fragmented, and the density functions in the two UMAP axes indicate concentration of plate clusters.",
    "After sphering, the UMAP plots in Fig. 6C show more integrated data points and better aligned density distributions of plates.",
    "The performance of the Cell Painting CNN in the biological matching task also improves upon the baselines (Fig. 6B) and displays a consistent ability to facilitate batch correction in all the three datasets, unlike the ImageNet CNN.",
    "We evaluated two alternative batch correction methods that use nonlinear transformations of features to remove unwanted variation: Harmony 39 and Gradient Reversal Layer 40 (GRL).",
    "The results indicate that these nonlinear batch correction methods do not improve the performance in the downstream analysis task, and in fact are unable to match sphering (Supplementary Fig. 5)."
  ],
